[{"id":"VR852769","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>Which of the following forces exerted on the disk, exert torques on the disk about Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>P</mtext></math></span></span> at the instant shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mn>1</mn> </math></span></span>?</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR852769_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A disk rolls without slipping down an incline as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. A force diagram, which represents the forces exerted on the disk and the locations at which the forces are exerted, is shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. At the instant shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mtext>P</mtext> </math></span></span>, which is on the edge of the disk is in contact with the incline.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. Figure 1 shows a disk rolling downward and to the left along a ramp, with the point of contact between the disk and the ramp labeled P. Figure 2 shows a force diagram overlaid over the disk on the ramp. An arrow labeled F sub friction extends from point P upward and to the right, along the surface of the ramp. An arrow labeled F sub normal extends from point P upward and to the left, through the center of the disk and perpendicular to the surface of the ramp. An arrow labeled F sub gravity extends from the center of the disk vertically downward\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR852769.g07.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The force of gravity only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The frictional force only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The frictional force and the gravitational force</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The frictional force, the gravitational force and the normal force</p>"],"answer":0}]